### Notes and References

The linguistic nuances are, of course, worth noting. [Middle English](/Middle_English) speakers would have pronounced it /ˈkæləs/, while in [West Flemish](/West_Flemish_language) it was Kales, and in [French](/French_language), Calaisis. The references, provided by various scholars, offer deeper dives into the specifics of this rather protracted English affair in France.